The World Conservation Union issued a warning at its congress in Bangkok, addressing the escalating extinction crisis.
They highlighted the impact of reef destruction on over a billion people, attributing it to human activities like climate change and species encroachment.
The South Asia marine coordinator emphasized the need to address poverty and population growth to prevent further degradation of coral reefs.
The devastation caused by tsunamis in South Asia has severely damaged marine ecosystems, with long-term recovery prospects.
Efforts to protect coral reefs include creating artificial reef areas and removing harmful debris to preserve marine life and tourism resources.
